<#
.SYNOPSIS
  SL-PATCH-3.0: Switch AI draft provider from Anthropic/Haiku to OpenAI (Responses API)

.DESCRIPTION
  Surgical replacement of Decision Engine section_d jsCode only.
  Section B (micro_intent / draft_policy) was wired by SL-PATCH-2.0 — untouched.
  Human Approval splice was applied by SL-PATCH-2.0 — untouched.
  All deterministic fallback templates preserved.
  AI never decides classification, safety, or send eligibility.
  Human approval remains mandatory.

  Changes vs SL-PATCH-2.0 section_d:
    - AI_DRAFT_PROVIDER = 'openai'
    - AI_DRAFT_MODEL    = 'gpt-5-mini' (configurable)
    - API key           = OPENAI_API_KEY env var
    - Endpoint          = https://api.openai.com/v1/responses (Responses API)
    - Auth header       = Authorization: Bearer <key>
    - Request body      = {model, input:[{role,content}], max_output_tokens, temperature?}
    - Response parsing  = data.output[0].content[0].text
    - AI JSON schema    = {draft_text, reasoning_summary, risk_flags:[]}
    - ai_attempt        adds provider and reasoning_summary / risk_flags fields
    - Temperature omitted if model rejects it (error falls back to deterministic)

.PARAMETER WhatIf
  Preview changes. No writes. Backup reads + offline tests only.

.PARAMETER Apply
  Execute: backup → deactivate → patch section_d → reactivate → offline tests → verify.

.NOTES
  Requires: HMZ_N8N_API_KEY env var
  Runtime only: OPENAI_API_KEY env var (not needed for the patch itself)
  Version: SL-PATCH-3.0
  Prerequisites: SL-PATCH-2.0 must have been applied (section_b + HA already patched)
#>

param(
    [switch]$WhatIf,
    [switch]$Apply
)

